comment:
Shanta, Let‚Äôs break down your claims here.

First, the idea that "there was no war for those 4 years" under Trump is misleading. While no new major wars were started, Trump‚Äôs administration saw escalated drone strikes in places like Yemen and Somalia, and nearly brought the U.S. to war with Iran after the killing of Iranian General Soleimani. So, the claim of a peaceful four years doesn‚Äôt hold up when you look at the full scope of his military actions.

Second, while Trump did donate his salary, he still profited from his businesses during his presidency, especially with his frequent trips to Trump properties, where taxpayer dollars were spent(Secret Service was charged for staying at his properties). This raised serious conflict-of-interest concerns, so it's not quite the selfless picture you're painting.

As for "most Democrats becoming billionaires," this is a baseless generalization. The Obamas, for instance, earned their wealth post-presidency through book deals and speaking engagements, which is a standard path for former presidents. 

And while Trump may have lost some personal wealth while in office, he continued to profit from his properties and brand exposure, so it‚Äôs not as simple as saying he "lost money."

Yes, Trump had some achievements, like signing the First Step Act for criminal justice reform, but there are also major criticisms, particularly his handling of the COVID-19 pandemic and policies like family separation at the border. So, it‚Äôs important to look at the full picture, not just cherry-pick favorable points. Stop being disingenuous, this orange guy would SA you in a heartbeat and deny you even existed.
